1. Search for Azure Database for MySQL flexible servers --> create --> Flexible server = advance create --> choose central us --> networking = for public acces no vnet required and for private
   vnet is required, click on Allow public access from any Azure service within Azure to this server, click Add current client IP  --> review and create.

2. After create copy the endpoint and you can connet through mysql workbench or with connect option --> create any database --> Go to settings and check all the options

3. Go to Replication --> Add replica --> give name and create it --> connect the reader --> check all the databases.

4. Go to compute and service --> you can increase Backup retention period to 35 days and save  --> Go to Backup and restore --> select on demand and create backup

2. Search for Storage Account --> give any unique name 

